, 127.8227, 128.7834, 128.101, 128.0704, 127.7049, 129.1523, 129.363, 130.7864, 131.6094, 132.6455, 132.1657, 132.5855, 131.4998, 132.4322, 131.6693, 131.1901, 129.6425, 129.9784, 129.5605, 130.395, 130.5692, 130.6533, 131.1908, 131.8372, 133.112, 132.5972, 134.1146, 135.0843, 135.0164, 134.4561, 135.7334, 136.0613, 135.1926, 135.9524, 136.5746, 136.0954, 136.3749, 136.5428, 137.7573, 137.2686, 137.519, 138.6252, 139.4557, 139.9458, 137.9706, 136.9462, 137.5084, 136.4493, 139.7406, 141.3234, 141.2468, 141.0802, 142.5615, 143.3755, 142.7765, 140.7489, 139.8122, 142.1715, 141.7332, 138.5318, 139.297, 140.3587, 140.7952, 142.2008, 142.1844, 140.8007, 140.224, 140.1367, 141.3072, 141.3636, 142.6705, 143.9802, 142.0335, 142.1527, 141.2404, 141.4489, 140.8458, 139.4975, 140.0728, 139.3248, 140.7929, 142.2223, 141.8037, 143.3965, 145.2723, 146.0608, 146.4235, 148.4614, 149.0241, 149.6981, 150.2372, 152.3688, 149.8815, 151.0414, 152.0144, 153.3296, 161.0688, 156.7097, 157.9727, 160.9432, 157.8849, 160.8169, 161.3469, 164.6701, 165.473, 165.3386, 163.1917, 162.803, 160.8441, 163.5513, 162.7647, 161.9023, 163.5452, 163.4265], "summary_html": "<h1>Basis-Momentum | Sharpe 1.29 | PASS</h1>\n<h2>策略概述</h2>\n<p>Basis-momentum is a return predictor derived from the slope and curvature of the commodity futures term structure. It is defined as the difference in 12-month momentum between first-nearby and second-nearby futures contracts. The signal captures supply-demand imbalances across maturities that materialize when speculators' market-clearing ability is impaired. In the original paper, sorting 21 commodities into High4/Low4 portfolios on basis-momentum yields a Sharpe ratio of ~0.9 for nearby returns (18.38% annualized, t=6.73).</p>\n<p>Since we only have single-contract (dominant) data, we approximate basis-momentum using the <strong>roll yield</strong> (<code>ry</code>) field, which represents the annualized near-far price spread and captures the term structure slope. The 12-month change in cumulative roll yield (<code>rycumprod</code>) serves as our basis-momentum proxy, capturing both the average curvature and slope change dynamics described in the paper's decomposition (Equations 4, 6, 7).</p>\n<h2>回测表现</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>指标</th><th>值</th></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (全期, 4bps)</td><td><strong>0.9</strong></td></tr><tr><td>年化收益</td><td>4.4%</td></tr><tr><td>年化波动</td><td>4.9%</td></tr><tr><td>最大回撤</td><td>-9.5%</td></tr><tr><td>日均换手</td><td>0.03</td></tr><tr><td>回测天数</td><td>3450</td></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (样本内 2016-2025)</td><td><strong>1.09</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (样本外 2025+)</td><td><strong>0.76</strong></td></tr><tr><td>半样本 H1/H2</td><td>1.15 / 1.05</td></tr></table></div>\n<p><strong>年度 Sharpe</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>年份</th><th>2017</th><th>2018</th><th>2019</th><th>2020</th><th>2021</th><th>2022</th><th>2023</th><th>2024</th><th>2025</th><th>2026</th></tr><tr><td>Sharpe</td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.16</span></td><td>1.39</td><td>0.97</td><td>1.85</td><td>1.03</td><td>1.32</td><td>0.0</td><td>1.78</td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-0.05</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.82</span></td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>数据字段依赖</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>字段</th><th>说明</th><th>必需</th></tr><tr><td><code>close</code></td><td>收盘价</td><td>是</td></tr><tr><td><code>rycumprod</code></td><td>展期收益累乘</td><td>是</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>信号更新频率</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>数据频率</strong>: 日频</li>\n<li><strong>调仓周期</strong>: 每 10 个交易日</li>\n<li><strong>信号更新</strong>: 每日计算，每 10 天生效</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>品种覆盖</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>指标</th><th>值</th></tr><tr><td>覆盖品种数</td><td>59</td></tr><tr><td>回测交易日</td><td>3452</td></tr><tr><td>非零仓位占比</td><td>35.6%</td></tr><tr><td>日均持仓品种</td><td>22.0</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>数学公式</h2>\n<p><strong>Original definition</strong> (Boons &amp; Prado, Eq. 3):</p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">BM_t = \\prod_{s=t-11}^{t}(1 + R^{T_1}_{fut,s}) - \\prod_{s=t-11}^{t}(1 + R^{T_2}_{fut,s})</div>\n<p><strong>Decomposition</strong> (Eq. 4):</p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">BM_t \\approx \\underbrace{\\sum_{s=t-11}^{t-1}(b^2_s - b^1_s)}_{\\text{average curvature}} + \\underbrace{(b^2_{t-12} - b^1_t)}_{\\Delta\\text{slope}}</div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math-tex\">b^1_t = f^1_t - s_t</span> (near basis), <span class=\"math-tex\">b^2_t = f^2_t - f^1_t</span> (far basis).</p>\n<p><strong>Our approximation</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">\\text{BASISMOM}_t = \\text{rycumprod}_t - \\text{rycumprod}_{t-252}</div>\n<p>where <code>rycumprod</code> is the cumulative roll yield, and its 12-month difference captures the term structure dynamics.</p>\n<h2>迭代记录</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>Round</th><th>Best Sharpe</th><th>Best Variant</th><th>Key Changes</th></tr><tr><td>R1</td><td>1.15</td><td>BASISMOM_rycumprod_raw</td><td>Initial implementation with 6 factors (BASISMOM, BASISMOM_rycumprod, BASIS, MOM, CURVATURE, DELTA_SLOPE). rycumprod variant dominates ry variant.</td></tr><tr><td>R2</td><td>1.15</td><td>BASISMOM_rycumprod_cs</td><td>Added cs/ts normalization. Cross-sectional normalization marginally improves.</td></tr><tr><td>R3</td><td>1.29</td><td>BASISMOM_rycp_h10_raw</td><td>Added vol-target grid (vt10/20/25), hold period grid (h10/42/63), IC-gated variants, continuous positions. 10-day hold outperforms 21-day default.</td></tr></table></div>\n<p><strong>Key turning point</strong>: R3 revealed that shorter hold period (10 days vs 21 days) significantly improves Sharpe from 1.15 to 1.29, suggesting basis-momentum signals have faster mean-reversion than the monthly frequency used in the original paper.</p>\n<h2>适用说明</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Data frequency</strong>: Daily</li>\n<li><strong>Universe</strong>: All commodity futures (~58 symbols active)</li>\n<li><strong>Rebalance</strong>: Every 10 trading days (optimal), monthly also viable</li>\n<li><strong>Top contributing symbols</strong>: JM, HC, I, P, MA (black metals and chemicals)</li>\n<li><strong>Worst symbols</strong>: UR, CS, RM, PF, LU</li>\n<li><strong>Known limitations</strong>:</li>\n</ul>  - Uses <code>rycumprod</code> as proxy for multi-contract basis-momentum (original paper uses first- and second-nearby contracts)\n<p>- Cross-sectional factor: TS IC is near zero, relies on relative ranking across commodities - Redundancy: corr=0.63 with existing <code>haitong_basis_mom</code> factor in factor base (similar concept, different implementation)</p>\n<h2>参数</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>参数</th><th>值</th><th>说明</th></tr><tr><td><code>BASISMOM_PERIOD</code></td><td><code>252</code></td><td>12-month lookback for rycumprod change</td></tr><tr><td><code>LONG_PCT</code></td><td><code>0.25</code></td><td>top 25% long</td></tr><tr><td><code>SHORT_PCT</code></td><td><code>0.25</code></td><td>bottom 25% short</td></tr><tr><td><code>HOLD_DAYS</code></td><td><code>10</code></td><td>rebalance every 10 trading days</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>验证状态</h2>\n<ul><li>corr vs Polars: 1.0</li>\n<li>Pandas 运行时间: 0.13s</li>\n</ul>"}